    <note>Ouyang(1) Hao [17873] Generational name and chronological logic would make him a lineage cousin of Ouyang(1) Xiu [1384] (probably miswritten as Ouyang(1) Guang in Xiu's jiapu [or vice versa]) and, therefore, a lineal descendant of Cong [3688]. Since Ouyang(1) Xiu drafts the funerary inscription for his father-in-law, Tang(2) Gong [3829] (q.v.), a probable close kinship connection seems likely. I am assuming that Hao and Guang were the same person (even if they are not, the kinship distances, etc. would be about the same), which would make both Xiu and Hao great grandsons of Bin [3687]. See Ouyang Xiu, WJ, 71.3a.</note>
